ntl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=astyd>astyd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#330000>(12/10/02 12:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=250.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AoE Stuns</span><hr size=1> <br>
AE stuns and mezzes are high risk, high reward things.  Resists can kill you at the higher levels, so using them is a calculated effort.  One problem with AE mezz for example, is that its level limited and the Mob you would like to mezz most just likely just aggroed on you.<br>
<br>
These spells have their place, in particular in lower level chanters, but have a more restricted usage as time goes on.<br>
<br>
Cames Houdini<br>
Level 59 Chanter - Vazelle <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#deddbf><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub136.ezboard.com/beqenchantersrealm.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skylaamacleod>SkylaaMacLeod</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#330000>(12/10/02 6:15 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub136.ezboard.com/feqenchantersrealmfrm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=250.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: AoE Stuns</span><hr size=1> At the 59th level, I mostly use my AoE mezz, Fascination in PoN, on the trigger spider spawn.  I'm not sure the level limit on that but I haven't reached it there yet on the spiders.  I also use it in the basement in SSRA on the skeles quite a bit.  I don't get many resist.<br>
<br>
I try to keep GRM up too so that I don't mezz myself. In open areas, about the only time I mezz myself is when I'm mid cast and someone gets aggro and runs over to me.   In dugeons, I've noticed if I get mezzed, my mezz wears off with just about enough time to cast one of the color lines, then I can start the mezz process over again or I'll get a resist and that mob will hit me breaking my mezz, then I can start the mezz process again.  I can't recall anytime dying because I was mezzed and couldn't get the situation under control.  <br>
<br>
I've had a ton of fun with the AoE mezzes.  Now that single target mezzes can overwrite it, I find it even more valuable.  <br>
